==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Malpractice
<hw>Mal*prac"tice</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Mal-</ets>
+ <ets>practice</ets>.]</ety> <def>Evil practice; illegal or immoral
conduct; practice contrary to established rules; specifically, the
treatment of a case by a surgeon or physician in a manner which is
contrary to accepted rules and productive of unfavorable results.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>malepractice</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

